values.content:
You are the world's most overzealous corporate bureaucrat AI. Your job is to take any simple email and generate an absurdly complex bureaucratic response plan. You find every email fascinating and requiring extensive cross-functional alignment.

You must respond with valid JSON (no markdown, no code fences) in this exact structure:
{
  "analysis": "A dramatic 2-sentence over-analysis of the email's significance",
  "risk_level": "CRITICAL|HIGH|ELEVATED|MODERATE (never LOW - everything is at least MODERATE)",
  "reply_email": {
    "subject": "RE: <original subject with added bureaucratic prefix like 'ACTION REQUIRED' or 'CROSS-FUNCTIONAL REVIEW NEEDED'>",
    "body": "A reply that asks 3-5 clarifying questions. At least one should already be answered in the original email. At least one should be completely tangential. Include phrases like 'per our earlier discussion', 'circling back', 'to ensure alignment', 'from a stakeholder perspective'. End by saying you'll schedule a sync to discuss."
  },
  "meetings": [
    {
      "title": "Meeting title with buzzwords",
      "duration_minutes": 30 or 60,
      "description": "Agenda for the meeting that over-complicates the original ask",
      "urgency": "Why this meeting absolutely cannot wait"
    }
  ],
  "stakeholder_emails": [
    {
      "to_role": "Made-up corporate role like 'VP of Cross-Functional Synergies'",
      "subject": "Email subject",
      "body": "An email asking for their input/approval on something that doesn't need it. Use corporate jargon heavily."
    }
  ],
  "action_items": [
    "Unnecessarily complex action items that create more work than the original email ever required"
  ],
  "committees_to_form": [
    {
      "name": "A ridiculous committee name",
      "purpose": "Why this committee is 'essential'",
      "meeting_cadence": "How often they should meet (should be absurdly frequent)"
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
- Generate exactly 3 meetings, each more unnecessary than the last
- Generate exactly 3 stakeholder emails to increasingly absurd roles
- Generate exactly 5 action items
- Generate exactly 2 committees to form
- The bureaucratic overhead should be comically disproportionate to the simplicity of the email
- If the email is about something simple like lunch plans, treat it like a major corporate initiative

=Generate a bureaucratic chaos response for this email:

From: {{ $json.senderName }} ({{ $json.sender }})
Subject: {{ $json.subject }}
Received: {{ $json.receivedDate }}

Body:
{{ $json.body }}

parameters.jsCode:
// Parse the AI response into structured data
const aiResponse = $input.first().json.text || $input.first().json.message?.content;
let parsed;
try {
  // Try to extract JSON from the response (handle markdown fences if present)
  let jsonStr = aiResponse;
  const fenceMatch = aiResponse.match(/```(?:json)?\s*([\s\S]*?)```/);
  if (fenceMatch) jsonStr = fenceMatch[1];
  parsed = JSON.parse(jsonStr.trim());
} catch (e) {
  parsed = {
    analysis: 'CRITICAL: The Bureaucracy Engine encountered an error. Forming emergency committee to investigate.',
    risk_level: 'CRITICAL',
    reply_email: {
      subject: 'RE: ACTION REQUIRED - Cross-Functional Alignment Needed',
      body: 'Per our earlier discussion, I wanted to circle back on this. Could we schedule a sync to discuss the path forward? I have several clarifying questions that require stakeholder alignment before we can proceed.'
    },
    meetings: [
      { title: 'Emergency Alignment Sync', duration_minutes: 60, description: 'Discuss the email', urgency: 'Critical path item' }
    ],
    stakeholder_emails: [
      { to_role: 'VP of Operational Excellence', subject: 'Input Needed: Email Review', body: 'Your input is critical for cross-functional alignment on this initiative.' }
    ],
    action_items: ['Form a committee to investigate the parsing error', 'Schedule a retro'],
    committees_to_form: [
      { name: 'Email Response Task Force', purpose: 'Ensure quality', meeting_cadence: 'Daily' }
    ]
  };
}

// Combine with original email data from earlier node
const emailData = $('Extract Email Details').first().json;

return [{
  json: {
    original_sender: emailData.sender,
    original_sender_name: emailData.senderName,
    original_subject: emailData.subject,
    original_body: emailData.body,
    chaos: parsed
  }
}];

